This file explains the licensing terms for Allacrost code and content. It also lists the appropriate attributions and 
licenses for third-party content that is used.


=====    Code      =====

All code is licensed under the GNU GPL Version 2 open source software license. Code is defined as anything contained within
the src/ and dat/ directories. Code includes both C++ and Lua source files.


=====   Content    =====

All original Allacrost content is licensed under the GNU GPL Version 2. Content is defined as anything contained within the img/,
snd/, and mus/ directories. Content includes PNG and JPEG images, WAV files, and Vorbis OGG music files.


=====   Sources    =====

Allacrost uses many pieces of content that were created external to the project and provided for use under a compatible license.
The following websites are where the majority of this content was procured from.

Identifier  Project                             Website
----------- ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
[BFW]       Battle for Wesnoth                  http://www.wesnoth.org
[FLR]       FLARE                               http://www.flare.org
[OGA]       OpenGameArt                         http://opengameart.org
[TIL]       Tiled Map Editor                    http://mapeditor.org/
[TMW]       TheManaWorld                        http://themanaworld.org/
[VAT]       Valyria Tear                        http://valyriatear.blogspot.com/


Note that some files may include multiple sources of content. Especially map tileset images. Such files may therefore be under
multiple licenses, and you should inquire which parts of the file correspond to what license prior to using this content.


=====   Licenses   =====

The following is a list of all files which contain artwork developed by a third-party. Please respect the original authors by
complying with the terms of their license before using their content. Any files not present in this list should be presumed to
be original Allacrost content and is provided under the terms of the Allacrost content license.

